  "text": "Nitrodopamine Priming by Ligand Exchange. Nitrodopamine (NDA) was used as anchor to prime the particles for grafting of aldehyde-poly(ethylene glycol) (ALD-PEG), as previously described. [CITATION_1] NDA was chosen as primer and dispersant anchor because of its demonstrated nondestructive and irreversible binding to Fe 3 O 4 NP surfaces. [CITATION_2] NDA was synthesized following a modified method published earlier. 34 Ligand exchange of oleic acid against NDA was performed in DMF at room temperature for 16 h. After three-fold precipitation with EtOH and centrifugation (5000 rpm/5 min), the fully NDA-coated NPs were dried under an N 2 stream.",
